{
  "text": "LCR and HCR rats reflect the complex nature of metabolic syndrome through extensive breeding for traits known to characterize both a healthy and poor metabolic state. The two strains can be divided based on their low and high health risk factors determined by their propensity to run greater or shorter distances based on their divergence in intrinsic aerobic capacity [CITATION_1] . To date, only male LCR and HCR rats have been studied related to peripheral nerve function [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , despite a higher incidence of chronic pain conditions in female patients [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
  "correct_citation": {
